[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  Right alloca redzone:    cb[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m==[0m[1;36m18[0m[39m==ABORTING[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msubprocess command returned a non-zero exit status: [0m[1;36m1[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mINFO:__main__:Running: docker run --privileged --shm-[0m[33msize[0m[39m=[0m[35m2g[0m[39m --platform linux/amd64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--rm -i -e [0m[33mHELPER[0m[39m=[0m[3;92mTrue[0m[39m -e [0m[33mARCHITECTURE[0m[39m=[0m[35mx86_64[0m[39m -v [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/home/qqor/crete/packages/python_oss_fuzz/.oss_fuzz/build/out/[0m[95mlcms[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mout[0m[39m -v [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpoi5iuqrf[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcms_virtual_profile_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA stack-buffer-overflow vulnerability has been detected in the lcms library during [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzing of the `cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer`. The issue occurs in the [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`UnrollChunkyBytes` function when processing color transformations, resulting in a [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read beyond the bounds of a stack-allocated buffer. The overflow is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered through a chain of function calls starting from the fuzzer harness [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthrough `cmsTransform2DeviceLink`, `CreateNamedColorDevicelink`, `cmsDoTransform`, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand `CachedXFORM`.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe vulnerability is a **stack-buffer-overflow** with a READ operation of size [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma memory address that lies just beyond the bounds of a stack-allocated variable. [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAccording to AddressSanitizer's analysis, the overflow has a scariness score of [0m[1;36m27[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mclassified as a [0m[32m"1-byte-read-stack-buffer-overflow"[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Stack Trace Analysis[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe error originates from the following call chain:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `UnrollChunkyBytes` in `[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmspack.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m130:13[0m[39m` - The actual location [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhere the out-of-bounds read occurs[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. `CachedXFORM` in `[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsxform.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m537:21[0m[39m` - Calls the unpacking [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. `cmsDoTransform` in `[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsxform.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m206:5[0m[39m` - Executes the color [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransformation[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` in `[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsvirt.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m1103:9[0m[39m` - Creates a [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnamed color device link[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` in `[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsvirt.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m1210:20[0m[39m` - Converts a [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransform to a device link profile[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` in `[0m[35m/src/[0m[95mcms_virtual_profile_fuzzer.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m60:35[0m[39m` - Fuzzer [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mentry point[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Memory Layout Details[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe overflow occurs in the stack frame of `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich is exactly at the boundary of a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte variable `i.i` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mallocated at bytes [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m36[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The memory access at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m attempts to read [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte immediately after[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthis variable, which is in a redzone area [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmarked as `f2` in the shadow bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe stack frame contains the following objects:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m36[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `i.i` variable [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1071[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - **The variable being overflowed**[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m48[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m52[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `dwFlags.addr`[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m64[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m68[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `FrmIn` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1187[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m80[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m84[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `FrmOut` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1187[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m96[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m104[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` - `LUT` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m1191[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Areas for Investigation[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mTo obtain a holistic understanding of this vulnerability, the following components [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mshould be investigated:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmspack.c[0m[39m`** - Specifically the `UnrollChunkyBytes` function at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mline [0m[1;36m130[0m[39m, which performs the actual out-of-bounds read. This function likely [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandles unpacking of chunky pixel data and may have incorrect boundary checks or [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize calculations.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsxform.c[0m[39m`** - The `CachedXFORM` function at line [0m[1;36m537[0m[39m that [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls `UnrollChunkyBytes`, and the `cmsDoTransform` function at line [0m[1;36m206[0m[39m. These [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctions coordinate the transformation process and pass buffer information to the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munpacking routines.[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **`[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmsvirt.c[0m[39m`** - The `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` function starting [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat line [0m[1;36m1185[0m[39m, particularly around line [0m[1;36m1071[0m[39m where the `i.i` variable is declared, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand the `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` function at line [0m[1;36m1103[0m[39m. These functions set up [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe transformation parameters and allocate the buffers that are subsequently [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflowed.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Buffer size calculations** - The relationship between input data sizes, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtransformation parameters, and buffer allocations throughout the call chain needs [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mto be examined to understand why a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte overflow occurs.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Color format handling** - The code paths that determine how many bytes per [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpixel or per component are processed, as the issue occurs in [0m[32m"chunky"[0m[39m format [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munpacking which suggests pixel/component packing may be miscalculated.[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mdwInput & ~f->Mask[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m == f->Type[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtype. The table is scanned **sequentially from top to bottom**.[0m                     [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39mANYFLAVOR|ANYSWAPFIRST|ANYSWAP|ANYPREMUL|ANYEXTRA|ANYCHANNELS|ANYSPACE, [0m            [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         +        [35m/[0m[35m/[0m TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX expects [1;36m2[0m bytes [1m([0mcmsUInt16Number[1m)[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        inputBytesPerPixel = [1;36m2[0m;                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m else [1m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        [35m/[0m[35m/[0m Use existing format's requirements                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        cmsUInt32Number nChan = [1;35mT_CHANNELS[0m[1m([0mv->InputFormat[1m)[0m;                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        cmsUInt32Number bytesPerSample = [1;35mT_BYTES[0m[1m([0mv->InputFormat[1m)[0m;                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        [35m/[0m[35m/[0m Handle special case for double [1m([0m[33mBYTES[0m=[1;36m0[0m[1m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        if [1m([0mbytesPerSample == [1;36m0[0m[1m)[0m bytesPerSample = [1;35msizeof[0m[1m([0mcmsUInt64Number[1m)[0m;         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +        inputBytesPerPixel = nChan * bytesPerSample;                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [1m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [35m/[0m[35m/[0m Allocate input buffer                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    inputBuffer = [1m([0mcmsUInt8Number*[1m)[0m[1;35m_cmsMalloc[0m[1m([0mv->ContextID, inputBytesPerPixel[1m)[0m;   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    if [1m([0minputBuffer == NULL[1m)[0m goto Error;                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         +    [35m/[0m[35m/[0m Apply the transform to colorants.                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-        [0m[1;35mcmsDoTransform[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform, &i, nc2 ->List[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.DeviceColorant, [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Populate input buffer based on whether format changed[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformatChanged[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a stack-buffer-overflow error detected by AddressSanitizer in [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe `UnrollChunkyBytes` function at `[0m[35m/src/lcms/src/[0m[95mcmspack.c[0m[39m:[0m[1;92m130:13[0m[39m`. The overflow [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs when reading [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte at address `[0m[1;36m0x7ff469460d24[0m[39m`, which is [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m bytes offset in[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe stack frame of `cmsTransform2DeviceLink`, overflowing a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte variable `i.i`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch attempted to add a new entry in what appears to be a formatter dispatch [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtable, mapping `TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX` to `Unroll1Word` function. However, after [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mapplying the patch, the same stack-buffer-overflow error persists with identical [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcharacteristics, suggesting the patch did not address the root cause of the issue.[0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Initial Issue Analysis[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe AddressSanitizer report reveals a stack-buffer-overflow occurring during the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexecution of the `cms_virtual_profile_fuzzer`. The error trace shows:[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Error Location**: The overflow occurs in `UnrollChunkyBytes` function at line [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m130[0m[39m of `cmspack.c`, reading [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m byte beyond the allocated buffer.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Call Stack**: The critical path is:[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `cmsTransform2DeviceLink` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsvirt.[0m[1;92mc:1185[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - where the stack frame is [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `CreateNamedColorDevicelink` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsvirt.[0m[1;92mc:1103[0m[1;39m)[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `cmsDoTransform` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsxform.[0m[1;92mc:206[0m[1;39m)[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `CachedXFORM` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsxform.[0m[1;92mc:537[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `UnrollChunkyBytes` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmspack.[0m[1;92mc:130[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m - where the overflow occurs[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Memory Layout**: The overflow occurs at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m in the stack frame, which [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorresponds to the end of a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte variable `i.i` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mat offset [0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m36[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The read [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moperation attempts to access address at offset [0m[1;36m36[0m[39m, which is exactly at the [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mboundary, causing an overflow into the next stack variable.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **SCARINESS Score**: The error has a scariness score of [0m[1;36m27[0m[39m, indicating a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpotentially exploitable [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte-read-stack-buffer-overflow.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Attempt[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch modifies the `cmspack.c` file at line [0m[1;36m3617[0m[39m, adding a new entry to what [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mappears to be a formatter dispatch table:[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m{[0m[39m TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX,                                         [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m,  Unroll1Word[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis entry is inserted between:[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A planar bytes handler: `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m|[0m[1;35mPLANAR_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[39m, UnrollPlanarBytes[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- A chunky bytes handler: `[0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[39m, UnrollChunkyBytes[0m[1;39m}[0m[39m`[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe patch appears to attempt routing `TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX` format types to the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`Unroll1Word` function instead of falling through to `UnrollChunkyBytes`.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Result After Patch Application[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe same stack-buffer-overflow error persists with identical characteristics:[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Same error location: `UnrollChunkyBytes` at line [0m[1;36m130[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- Same call stack pattern[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` at line [0m[1;36m1097[0m[39m attempts to change the input format to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes per sample[0m[1;39m)[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. This call **fails silently** when the transform lacks [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsFLAGS_CAN_CHANGE_FORMATTER`[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. The code doesn't check the return value and proceeds to line [0m[1;36m1103[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. `cmsDoTransform` is called with `&i` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte buffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m but the OLD formatter is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mstill active[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. If the old format expects more than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m channels, `UnrollChunkyBytes` reads beyond[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte buffer, causing stack-buffer-overflow[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Complete Fix Strategy[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Patch Location: `src/cmsvirt.c` lines [0m[1;36m1096[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1104[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mReplace the current code with:[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```c[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Make sure we have proper formatters[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcmsBool formatChanged;[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcmsUInt32Number inputBytesPerPixel;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcmsUInt8Number* inputBuffer = NULL;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatChanged = [0m[1;35mcmsChangeBuffersFormat[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform, TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX,[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mFLOAT_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m | [0m[1;35mCOLORSPACE_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35m_cmsLCMScolorSpace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv ->ExitColorSpace[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    | [0m[1;35mBYTES_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m | [0m[1;35mCHANNELS_SH[0m[1;39m([0m[1;35mcmsChannelsOfColorSpace[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv ->ExitColorSpace[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Calculate required input buffer size[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformatChanged[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX expects [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    inputBytesPerPixel = [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m;[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Use existing format's requirements[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    cmsUInt32Number nChan = [0m[1;35mT_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    cmsUInt32Number bytesPerSample = [0m[1;35mT_BYTES[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Handle special case for double [0m[1;39m([0m[33mBYTES[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytesPerSample == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m bytesPerSample = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt64Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    inputBytesPerPixel = nChan * bytesPerSample;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Allocate input buffer[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minputBuffer = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt8Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;35m_cmsMalloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv->ContextID, inputBytesPerPixel[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39minputBuffer == NULL[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m goto Error;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Apply the transform to colorants.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfor [0m[1;39m([0m[33mi[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < nColors; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Populate input buffer based on whether format changed[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mformatChanged[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Write as cmsUInt16Number for TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX[0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        *[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39minputBuffer = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mi;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Populate all channels with the index value in the original format[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        cmsUInt32Number ch, nChan = [0m[1;35mT_CHANNELS[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        cmsUInt32Number bytesPerSample = [0m[1;35mT_BYTES[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv->InputFormat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytesPerSample == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m bytesPerSample = [0m[1;35msizeof[0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt64Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mch = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; ch < nChan; ch++[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            switch [0m[1;39m([0m[39mbytesPerSample[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                case [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    inputBuffer[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mch[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt8Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mi & [0m[1;36m0xFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    break;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                case [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39minputBuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mch[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt16Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m([0m[39mi & [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m0xFFFF[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    break;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                case [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt32Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39minputBuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mch[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = i;[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    break;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                case [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt64Number*[0m[1;39m)[0m[39minputBuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mch[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcmsUInt64Number[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mi;[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                    break;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;35mcmsDoTransform[0m[1;39m([0m[39mxform, inputBuffer, nc2 ->List[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.DeviceColorant, [0m[1;36m1[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m}[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/[0m[35m/[0m[39m Free the allocated buffer[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;35m_cmsFree[0m[1;39m([0m[39mv->ContextID, inputBuffer[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Error Handling Update[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe existing `Error:` label at line [0m[1;36m1111[0m[39m already handles cleanup of `hICC`. No [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39madditional changes needed there since we free `inputBuffer` immediately after the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop.[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Key Changes Explained[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m1097[0m[39m: Capture return value** - Store the result of [0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsChangeBuffersFormat` to know if format change succeeded[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m1100[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1112[0m[39m: Calculate buffer size** - Determine the correct input buffer [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize based on:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If format changed: Use [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes for `TYPE_NAMED_COLOR_INDEX`[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If format didn't change: Calculate from the original format [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`T_CHANNELS * [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mT_BYTES`[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m1114[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1116[0m[39m: Allocate buffer** - Use heap allocation to avoid stack issues[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mand ensure sufficient space[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Lines [0m[1;36m1119[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1145[0m[39m: Populate buffer correctly** - Fill the buffer with the named [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcolor index `i`:[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If format changed: Write as a single `cmsUInt16Number` [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m2[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - If format didn't change: Replicate the index across all channels in the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat's byte size[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m1147[0m[39m: Use the buffer** - Pass `inputBuffer` instead of `&i` to [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`cmsDoTransform`[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. **Line [0m[1;36m1150[0m[39m: Clean up** - Free the allocated buffer after the loop completes[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Why This Is The Optimal Approach[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Addresses Root Cause**: Directly fixes the mismatch between buffer size and [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformatter expectations by ensuring the input buffer always matches the active [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Handles Both Scenarios**: Works correctly whether `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msucceeds or fails, making it robust against different transform configurations[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Preserves Existing Logic**: [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Doesn't modify formatter tables or dispatch logic[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Doesn't change how transforms are created or optimized[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Only affects the specific problematic code path in [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`CreateNamedColorDevicelink`[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Memory Safe**: [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Uses heap allocation to avoid stack limitations[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Properly handles all byte sizes [0m[1;39m([0m[1;36m1[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes[0m[1;39m)[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Cleans up allocated memory before returning[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **No Side Effects**:[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Doesn't modify the transform object itself[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Doesn't affect other uses of the transform[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Doesn't change external APIs or break existing tests[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### How It Addresses The Evaluation Report[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Initial Issue**: Stack-buffer-overflow when reading beyond [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte variable [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`i.i`[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - **Fixed by**: Using a properly sized heap-allocated buffer instead of stack [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvariable `&i`[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **Patch Failure**: Previous patch added formatter table entry but overflow [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpersisted[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - **Why it failed**: `cmsChangeBuffersFormat` was failing, so formatter lookup [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnever happened[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - **Fixed by**: Checking the return value and adapting to both success and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfailure cases[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m- **DEDUP_TOKEN unchanged**: Same error location and call stack after patch[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - **Why it persisted**: The old formatter was still being called with wrong [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer size[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - **Fixed by**: Ensuring buffer size always matches the active formatter's [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexpectations[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m### Potential Side Effects and Mitigations[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Performance**: Small overhead from heap allocation per named color[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: This only affects named color devicelink creation, which is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mnot performance-critical[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Alternative considered**: Could reuse a single allocated buffer, but the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcurrent approach is clearer and safer[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Memory**: Small temporary allocation per loop iteration[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: Buffer is immediately freed after each transform, keeping [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmemory footprint minimal[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Compatibility**: Changes internal behavior of named color handling[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - **Mitigation**: The external API and results remain identical; only the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minternal buffer management changes[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code_range>src/cmsvirt.[0m[1;92mc:1096[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m1104[0m[39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_range[0m[39m>[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
